<sect1 id="apiref.nfgsupport">
<title>Supports of normal form strategies</title>

<para>
</para>

<sect2 id="apiref.nfgsupport.addstrategy">
<title>AddStrategy</title>
<indexterm><primary>AddStrategy</primary></indexterm>

<formalpara>
<title>GCL usage</title>
<para>
<synopsis>
AddStrategy[support->NFSUPPORT, strategy->STRATEGY] =: NFSUPPORT 
</synopsis>
</para>
</formalpara>

<para>
<function>AddStrategy</function> adds <parameter>strategy</parameter>
to the <parameter>support</parameter>.  If the strategy is already in
the support, no change is made.  A copy of the modified support is
returned.  It is an error if <parameter>support</parameter> and
<parameter>strategy</parameter> are not from the same normal form
game.
</para>

</sect2>


<sect2 id="apiref.nfgsupport.getlabel">
<title>GetLabel</title>
<indexterm><primary>GetLabel</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>Name (GCL function)</primary></indexterm>

<formalpara>
<title>C++/Python usage</title>
<para>
<synopsis>
gText gbtNfgSupport::GetLabel(void) const
</synopsis>
</para>
</formalpara>

<formalpara>
<title>GCL usage</title>
<para>
<synopsis>
Name[x->NFSUPPORT] =: TEXT
</synopsis>
</para>
</formalpara>

<para>
<function>GetLabel</function> (<function>Name</function> in the GCL)
returns the text label of the support.
</para>

</sect2>


<sect2 id="apiref.nfgsupport.removestrategy">
<title>RemoveStrategy</title>
<indexterm><primary>RemoveStrategy</primary></indexterm>

<formalpara>
<title>RemoveStrategy</title>
<para>
<synopsis>
RemoveStrategy[support->NFSUPPORT, strategy->STRATEGY] =: NFSUPPORT 
</synopsis>
</para>
</formalpara>

<para>
<function>RemoveStrategy</function> 
removes <parameter>strategy</parameter> from <parameter>support</parameter>.
If <parameter>strategy</parameter> is not in
the support, there is no effect.  A copy of the modified support is
returned.  It is an error if <parameter>support</parameter> and 
<parameter>strategy</parameter> are
not from the same normal form game, or if removing <parameter>strategy</parameter> would result in the support containing no strategies for a player.
</para>

</sect2>


<sect2 id="apiref.nfgsupport.setlabel">
<title>SetLabel</title>
<indexterm><primary>SetLabel</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary>SetName (GCL function)</primary></indexterm>

<formalpara>
<title>C++/Python usage</title>
<para>
<synopsis>
void gbtNfgSupport::SetLabel(const gText &amp;p_label)
</synopsis>
</para>
</formalpara>

<formalpara>
<title>GCL usage</title>
<para>
<synopsis>
SetName[x->NFSUPPORT, name->TEXT] =: NFSUPPORT
</synopsis>
</para>
</formalpara>

<para>
<function>SetLabel</function> (<function>SetName</function> in the GCL) 
sets the text label of the support.  The GCL version returns the player.
</para>

</sect2>

<sect2 id="apiref.nfgsupport.undominated">
<title>UnDominated</title>
<indexterm><primary>UnDominated</primary></indexterm>

<formalpara>
<title>GCL usage</title>
<para>
<synopsis>
UnDominated[support->NFSUPPORT, {strong->False}, 
            {mixed->False}, {precision->Rational}, {time<->0.000000}, 
            {traceFile<->(Output)}, {traceLevel->0}] =: NFSUPPORT 
</synopsis>
</para>
</formalpara>

<para>
<function>UnDominated</function>
finds dominated strategies in the 
<parameter>support</parameter>. 
The returned support contains only the undominated
strategies or actions; if this support is identical to the input support,
no strategies were found to be dominated.  The following
optional parameters may be specified to modify the behavior of
the elimination:
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>
<parameter>strong</parameter> By default, all weakly dominated
strategies are eliminated.  If this is specified
<literal>True</literal>, elimination is based on strict dominance.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>
<parameter>mixed</parameter>: By default, elimination is done in pure
strategies.  If this is specified <literal>True</literal>,
elimination is done by examining mixtures over other strategies.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>
<parameter>precision</parameter>: Default precision is rational.  Note
that the precision parameter is only applicable for mixed domination.
Pure strategy domination always uses rational precision.
</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>

</sect2>

</sect1>

